      <description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;Hatchet has a very "WoW"ish pathing, ie, if you strafe at&#xD;
certain points he will turn around, run back to some checkpoint and&#xD;
then come rushing at you once again. We noticed it more by misstake and&#xD;
frustration during both the chase part and the trapping part trying to&#xD;
trap him, but it's quite probable that strafing back will cause him to&#xD;
once again run to the checkpoint, creating a "WoW"ish crowdcontrol&#xD;
measure, where pathing is so bad you can control a mob indefintly by&#xD;
strafing back and forth. That &lt;i&gt;could&lt;/i&gt; completely trivialise the&#xD;
chase part of the fight if someone would find out which area or&#xD;
movements causes this disruption in movement. However, the more&#xD;
annoying part that everyone faces is when he goes running back as you&#xD;
try to trap him, leading him to occationally become rooted far away.&lt;br&gt;He&#xD;
also sometimes refuses to follow someone running to fast (ie, has the&#xD;
blockers) and instead takes a (rather admitedly) more clever path,&#xD;
making kiting him a semi prayer that you don't run over one of the&#xD;
points that will make him switch heading. The fight should be easier&#xD;
with blockers, not harder, aye?&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
